  "prompt": "Will I be arrested reentering the US with a bench warrant?",
  "response": "If you have an active bench warrant in the United States and you attempt to reenter the country, there is a possibility that you could be detained or arrested upon entry. Bench warrants typically arise from failing to appear in court or failing to comply with court orders, and they give law enforcement the authority to arrest you.\n\nWhen reentering the U.S., customs and border protection officials have access to databases that may include information about active warrants. If they discover a warrant for your arrest, they may detain you and turn you over to the appropriate authorities.\n\nTo avoid potential arrest, it is advisable to resolve any outstanding warrants before attempting to enter the U.S. You might consider consulting with an attorney who can provide legal advice specific to your situation and help you address the warrant.",
